Package graphanalyzer.controller.routines

Class StronglyConnectedComponentsRoutine

  • java.lang.Object
    • graphanalyzer.controller.routines.StronglyConnectedComponentsRoutine
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AlgorithmRoutine, java.io.Serializable
    public class StronglyConnectedComponentsRoutine
extends java.lang.Object
implements AlgorithmRoutine
    Routine for a algorithm that computes the Strongly Connected Components of a directed graph.

    Implementation of the interface AlgorithmRoutine that is mainly based around a "state machine." The state machine is implemented by a simple enum StronglyConnectedComponentsRoutine.STATE. It has three values:

    1. FIRST: Displays the first depth first search of the algorithm.
    2. TRANSPOSE: Displays the transposed graph.
    3. SECOND: Displays the second depth first search of the algorithm.
    Author:
    paulehler
    See Also:
    AlgorithmRoutine, Serialized Form
